<dl id="n54144c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54144c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54144c"> 144(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> substitute <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54144c"><li>FW 28.35 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n54144c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n54144c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54144c">MS BL 47476b-469</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:275 <a name="ad8" href="../../ff/fdra/ada.htm#ad8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad8.htm#n54144c">Draft: I.1&sect;1.8</a>/2.8</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Dans un certain nombre de tribus de la Nigeria du Nord, l&apos;usage de ce genre de symboles est courant. M. Meek leur donne le nom de <mark>substituts</mark>. &laquo;Il n&apos;est gu&egrave;re douteux que ces pots et ces pierres soient des substituts des cr&acirc;nes des anc&ecirc;tres. Chaque chef de famille a une hutte sp&eacute;ciale o&ugrave; sont plac&eacute;s les symboles &mdash; le plus souvent des pots, parfois des pierres. Chacun repr&eacute;sente un anc&ecirc;tre. Pourtant ces symboles ne remontent pas au del&agrave; de la g&eacute;n&eacute;ration pr&eacute;c&eacute;dente; un homme ne se pr&eacute;occupe pas de ses grands-p&egrave;res. Son attention se limite aux p&egrave;res et aux oncles maternels qui sont morts.&raquo; <br><font color="green">[In a number of tribes in northern Nigeria, the use of such symbols is common. Mr. Meek gives them the name of substitutes. "There is little doubt that these pots and stones are substitutes for the skulls of the ancestors. Each head of the family has a special hut where the symbols are placed&mdash;most often pots, sometimes stones. Each represents an ancestor. Yet these symbols do not go back beyond the previous generation; a man does not care about his grandfathers. His attention is limited to the fathers and maternal uncles who died."]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 217</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
